main event: An observer sighted a rectangular object in Osterville, Massachusetts on April 10, 1966.
interesting points: The observer described the object as 2 feet long and 1 foot wide,The sighting lasted for only 5 seconds,The object traveled from 20 degrees elevation in the north to 20 degrees elevation in the south,No sound was observed during the sighting,The conclusion of the report is that the object was a meteor.
witness description: The observer seemed sincere and frank during the telephone interview.
